==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''lambda expression'''

# An algebraic expression representing a function by binding one or more [[parameter]]s to an expression which may contain those parameters.

===Examples===

<table border="1">
<tr><th>Expression</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td><math>\lambda x.1</math></td><td>The constant value 1</td></tr>
<tr><td><math>\lambda x.x</math></td><td>The [[identity]]</td></tr>
<tr><td><math>\lambda x.x+1</math></td><td><math>f(x)=x+1</math></td></tr>
<tr><td><math>\lambda n.\lambda x.x+n</math></td><td><math>f(n) = g</math> where <math>g(x) = x+n</math></td></tr>
</table>